Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
editChangeVia(25.10)                                      editChangeVia(25.10)

Name
       editChangeVia  - Replaces the selected vias or the vias listed in -from
       with the specified vias or with vias having the specified cut class and
       pattern

Syntax
       editChangeVia

       [-help]

       [-net <net_name>]

       [-signal_only {0 | 1}]

       {[-from <string> [-area {<x1 y1 x2 y2>} | -at {<x y>} ]] | [-selected]}

       {-to <string> | [-via_columns <integer> -via_rows <integer> [-cut_class
       <class_name>]]}

       Replaces the selected vias or the vias listed in -from with the  speci-
       fied vias or with vias having the specified cut class and pattern.

       While  modifying  a via with editChangeVia, the setEditMode -drc_on and
       -keep_via settings are used in combination to decide whether or  not  a
       via should be replaced if the new via cell results in DRC violations:

              * setEditMode -drc_on false

                With  this  setting,  the  tool does not check for Design Rule
                Check (DRC) violations when you modify a  via  using  the  ed-
                itChangeVia command.

              * setEditMode -drc_on true -keep_via false

                With  this setting, the tool checks for DRC violations and al-
                lows you to replace the via even if the new via is  generating
                violations. The DRC violations are displayed on the layout.

              * setEditMode -drc_on true -keep_via true

                With  this setting, the tool checks for DRC violations and re-
                tains the original via if the new  one  is  generating  viola-
                tions.

       The  behavior  defined above applies for all via modifications with ed-
       itChangeVia, irrespective of whether you use the -to <string> option or
       the -via_columns <integer> -via_rows <integer> options.

       Note that the setEditMode -drc_on true option does not check cut  spac-
       ing, enclosure spacing, or other geometry of the via cell itself.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each editChangeVia parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man editChangeVia

       -area {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}
              Specifies  the  coordinates  of the area in which vias are to be
              replaced. If a via indicated by the -from parameter is  in  this
              area, replaces the via with the via indicated by the -to parame-
              ter.

       -at {<x y>}
              Specifies  the  coordinates  for the origin of the via to be re-
              placed. The via at this location is replaced by  the  via  indi-
              cated by the -to parameter.

       -cut_class <class_name>
              Specifies the cut class of the replacement vias.

       -from <string>
              Specifies  a  via  or  list  of vias to replace. Enclose the via
              names on the list in curly braces and separate each name with  a
              space.  Vias  whose  masters are not specified in string are not
              changed.

              Notes:

              * You must specify the -from or the -selected parameter. If  you
                do  not specify at least one of these parameters, the software
                does not change any vias.

              * The number of via names on the -from list must be equal to the
                number of via names on the -to list. In addition,  the  corre-
                sponding pair of vias in each list must be on the same layer.

       -net <net_name>
              Specifies the net name on which to change vias.

       -selected
              Replace vias for selected ones only.

              Note:  You must specify the -from or the -selected parameter. If
              you do not specify at least one of these parameters,  the  soft-
              ware does not change any vias.

       -signal_only {1 | 0}
              Specifies  whether  signal  vias only or signal and special vias
              are changed. Specify 1 to change signal via only. Specify  0  to
              change signal and special vias.

              Default: 0

       -to <string>
              Specifies  a via or a list of vias to replace the vias indicated
              by the -from parameter. If you specify more than  one  via,  en-
              close  the  via  list in curly braces and separate each via name
              with a space.

              Note: The number of via names on the list must be the  equal  to
              the  number of via names on the list for the -from parameter. In
              addition, the corresponding pair of vias in each list must be on
              the same layer.

       -via_columns <integer>
              Specifies the number of columns in the replacement vias.

       -via_rows <integer>
              Specifies the number of rows in the replacement vias.

Examples
              * The following command changes all VIA_XX vias of the net  VDD1
                located within a specified region to VIA_YY vias:

                editChangeVia  -net  VDD1 -area {x1 y1 x2 y2} -from VIA_XX -to
                VIA_YY

              *

                The following command replaces the  selected  vias  with  vias
                having a cut pattern of 3 by 3:

                editChangeVia -selected -via_columns 3 -via_rows 3

